There are three things in this column:
- lines between the individual timeline orbs

The big timeline orbs act as navigation for the history tabs we just filled out. There are four of them. You can add more if you know what you're doing (they use Bootstrap v4.3 vertical pills). These are denoted with a ""xxx A.E.D. - Section X"". To edit them, first edit the ""000"" in the code directly BELOW (I can't put it on a separate line for you, sorry) to contain the year you want the event to take place in. Then fill in the same year into the ""xxx A.E.D - Section X"", and name the section something. So for example, if your character gets a promotion in 502 A.E.D., you'll edit the 000 to say 502, and then edit the label to say ""502 A.E.D. - Got promoted"". Do NOT add 'A.E.D.' into the 000 container, it won't fit.

The small timeline orbs just display a message upon hover. They're marked with ""xxx A.E.D. - Event"". Keep the description brief (5-6 WORDS maximum) since the tooltip it displays in isn't meant for longer texts.
You can effectively move the orbs around by copying and pasting the div elements with a clip-path between them. These elements act as the lines in the timeline.

By the time I got to this section, I had run out of music to listen to so I dug into my 2011 playlists and listened to Cash Cash on repeat. That's how long this took.

Welcome to the personality section. Nothing extreme going on here, we have 3 positive traits, 3 neutral ones, 3 negative ones. You can copy and paste the trait container in each section to expand it, but keep in mind that the box is narrow so if your super developed character has 35 traits or something, the box will be gigantic, and then you'll have broken the layout, and then I'm not responsible.

Welcome to the Extra Info/Miscellaneous info tab. The first text you'll use here will be pasted where that Lorem Ipsum paragraph is.

Right under there is the mini-moodboard. Choose four images that you feel represent your character and paste them there. Again, the frames are tiny, so ideally go for small (70x70px) images. If you paste a 2k x 1k wallpaper in there, I'm going to cry.

Under the moodboard are two theme song buttons. Paste the link to the theme songs of your choice there, and change the text to match the name of the song. It won't make a music player on the TH profile itself, since I'm not a huge fan of having no control over the progress/volume of the song and I also like to see what I'm clicking to play instead of just trusting that it's a nice song. I feel like that's a long explanation for a feature as small as this, but here you go anyway.

Under the theme song buttons is the Extra notes section. Feel free to add more notes, just remember to enclose them in
  • brackets.

Almost done! Isn't that exciting? This is a tab where you can put your character's family members. If your character has a massive family tree with 250 relatives, please choose the three most important ones - you see that ""LINK GOES HERE"" at the bottom? You can paste your family doc link in there and anyone can read all about your character's great-great-great-great uncles there. Or, if you're so inclined, look up how to add tabs in Bootstrap and add them into the code to include more family members. That is 100% on you though.

Like before, replace the link to the wikimedia image with a link to an icon of the given family members (or leave it as the wikimedia image, if you don't have a picture), replace the name/surname, and add a small description.

These are the relationship cards at the bottom of the ref. The first thing you'll paste into here is the link to an image of the character in question. The box is tiny, and while it won't overflow if you paste a bigger image into it, using too many large images will slow down the page, so crop any big images to fit a roughly 100x100px circle.
The second thing you'll edit is the relationship icon and relationship status. Here is a list of them:

Next is the Name and Surname, pretty straightforward. Then you'll want to write one or two sentences of what your character thinks about this character. You can describe the relationship in more detail in the box under that.
The last section looks complicated, but I promise it's easier than it appears. These are the four relationship bars you see at the bottom of each card. They're in this order:
To edit them, simply edit the four percentages in this order. Choose numbers between 0% and 100%, obviously.
